---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Contact | productliabilitycalc.com';
const description = 'Contact the productliabilitycalc.com editorial team. Editorial questions, corrections, licensing, and press inquiries.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Contact</h1>
  <p><em>Updated May 2026.</em></p>

  <p>The fastest way to reach us is by email: <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>. We typically respond within two business days. We do not run a chat widget or a phone line; email is the only channel.</p>

  <h2>What we respond to</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Corrections to specific page content.</strong> Include the page URL and the exact claim you believe is wrong, with a source if you have one. We act on these quickly.</li>
    <li><strong>Editorial questions about methodology.</strong> If you are trying to understand why the calculator produced a particular range, or what a specific multiplier means, ask. We will explain.</li>
    <li><strong>Licensing inquiries.</strong> If you would like to republish a guide, embed the calculator, or use a substantial excerpt in print or in a course, contact us.</li>
    <li><strong>Press inquiries.</strong> If you are a journalist working on a product liability or mass-tort story and want background, we are happy to talk on or off the record.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we cannot help with</h2>

  <p>We are not a law firm. The contributors are not licensed attorneys and cannot give legal advice or take cases. If you have a specific product liability matter, you need a licensed product liability attorney in your state. Local bar associations maintain lawyer-referral services and most plaintiff-side product liability firms offer free initial consultations.</p>

  <p>We also do not provide case-valuation services beyond what the calculator on this site produces. If you want a personalized estimate, that conversation has to happen with a lawyer who can review the actual facts.</p>

  <h2>Mailing address</h2>

  <p>The Click Lab operates as a digital-only publisher. For legal or contractual notices that require a postal address, request one by email and we will provide it.</p>
</BaseLayout>
